      "note": "In 26:187, Shu'ayb, the Prophet of Allah, is challenged by the Companions of the Wood \"to cause a piece of sky to fall on us, if thou art truthful.\" Such a challenge, in some form or other, is addressed to all Prophets of Allah. It is mere defiance. It has no meaning. If a piece of the sky were to fall on them, it would not convince them, for they would only say: \"These are only clouds gathered in heaps.\" They do not wish to believe. Otherwise there are ample Signs and Evidences of Allah's Plan in Creation and in man's own heart."
